55 /*!

1283 
1284  // All of the addXxxOptions take in the name of the option, and a reference to the field of that option
1285  // in the option structure. Depending on the specific type, it may take in a default value, and may
1286  // take in extra options. The addXxxOptions mostly follow the same pattern, so please see addDoubleOption
1287  // for detailed comments.
1288  //
1289  // List options are those that can be an unknown number of elements, and also take in a reference to
1290  // an integer. This integer will be populated with the number of elements of that type unmarshaled.
1291  //
1292  // Array options are those with a fixed number of elements.
1293  //
1294  // List and Array options should also be able to be specified with the string "NONE" indicating that there
1295  // are no elements. This allows the option to be present in a config file but left blank.
1296 
1297  /*!< \brief addDoubleOption creates a config file parser for an option with the given name whose
1298  value can be represented by a su2double.*/
1299 
1300  void addDoubleOption(const string& name, su2double & option_field, su2double default_value);
1301 
1302  void addStringOption(const string& name, string & option_field, string default_value);
1303 
1304  void addIntegerOption(const string& name, int & option_field, int default_value);
1305 
1306  void addUnsignedLongOption(const string& name, unsigned long & option_field, unsigned long default_value);
1307 
1308  void addUnsignedShortOption(const string& name, unsigned short & option_field, unsigned short default_value);
1309 
1310  void addLongOption(const string& name, long & option_field, long default_value);
1311 
1312  void addBoolOption(const string& name, bool & option_field, bool default_value);
1313 
1314  // enum types work differently than all of the others because there are a small number of valid
1315  // string entries for the type. One must also provide a list of all the valid strings of that type.
1316  template <class Tenum, class Tfield>
1317  void addEnumOption(const string name, Tfield& option_field, const map<string,Tenum>& enum_map, Tenum default_value);
1318

1499  /*!
1500  * \brief Get reference origin for moment computation.
1501  * \param[in] val_marker - the marker we are monitoring.
1502  * \return Reference origin (in cartesians coordinates) for moment computation.
1503  */
1504  std::array<su2double,3> GetRefOriginMoment(unsigned short val_marker) const {
1505  std::array<su2double,3> RefOriginMoment{{0.0}};
1506  if(val_marker < nMarker_Monitoring) {
1507  RefOriginMoment[0] = RefOriginMoment_X[val_marker];
1508  RefOriginMoment[1] = RefOriginMoment_Y[val_marker];
1509  RefOriginMoment[2] = RefOriginMoment_Z[val_marker];
1510  }
1511  return RefOriginMoment;
1512  }
1513 
1514  /*!
1515  * \brief Get reference origin x-coordinate for moment computation.
1516  * \param[in] val_marker - the marker we are monitoring.
1517  * \return Reference origin x-coordinate (in cartesians coordinates) for moment computation.
1518  */
1519  su2double GetRefOriginMoment_X(unsigned short val_marker) const { return RefOriginMoment_X[val_marker]; }
1520

1527

1534

2168  /*!
2169  * \brief Get the flame initialization.
2170  * (x1,x2,x3) = flame offset/spark center location.
2171  * (x4,x5,x6) = flame normal, separating unburnt from burnt or
2172  * spark radius, spark start iteration, spark duration.
2173  * (x7) = flame thickness, the length from unburnt to burnt conditions.
2174  * (x8) = flame burnt thickness, the length to stay at burnt conditions.
2175  * \return Ignition initialization parameters for the flamelet model.
2176  */
2177  const su2double* GetFlameInit() const {
2178  switch (flame_init_type)
2179  {
2180  case FLAMELET_INIT_TYPE::FLAME_FRONT:
2181  return flame_init.data();
2182  break;
2183  case FLAMELET_INIT_TYPE::SPARK:
2184  return spark_init.data();
2185  break;
2186  default:
2187  return nullptr;
2188  break;
2189  }
2190  }
2191

2969  * \brief Get the number of design variables.
2970  * \return Number of the design variables.
2971  */
2972  unsigned short GetnDV_Value(unsigned short iDV) const {
2973  if (!nDV_Value) return 0;
2974  return nDV_Value[iDV];
2975  }
2976 
2977  /*!
2978  * \brief Get the total number of design variables.
2979  */
2980  unsigned short GetnDV_Total(void) const {
2981  if (!nDV_Value) return 0;
2982  unsigned short sum = 0;
2983  for (unsigned short iDV = 0; iDV < nDV; iDV++) {
2984  sum += nDV_Value[iDV];
2985  }
2986  return sum;
2987  }

3827  /*!
3828  * \brief Governing equations of the flow (it can be different from the run time equation).
3829  * \param[in] val_zone - Zone where the soler is applied.
3830  * \return Governing equation that we are solving.
3831  */
3832  MAIN_SOLVER GetKind_Solver(void) const { return Kind_Solver; }
3833 
3834  /*!
3835  * \brief Return true if a fluid solver is in use.
3836  */
3837  bool GetFluidProblem(void) const {
3838  switch (Kind_Solver) {
3839  case MAIN_SOLVER::EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::RANS:
3840  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS:
3841  case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
3842  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS:
3843  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS:
3844  return true;
3845  default:
3846  return false;
3847  }
3848  }
3849 
3850  /*!
3851  * \brief Return true if a structural solver is in use.
3852  */
3853  bool GetStructuralProblem(void) const {
3854  return (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY) || (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM);
3855  }
3856 
3857  /*!
3858  * \brief Return true if a heat solver is in use.
3859  */
3860  bool GetHeatProblem(void) const {
3861  return (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::HEAT_EQUATION) || (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_HEAT);
3862  }
3863 
3864  /*!
3865  * \brief Return true if a high order FEM solver is in use.
3866  */
3867  bool GetFEMSolver(void) const {
3868  switch (Kind_Solver) {
3869  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS: case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_LES:
3870  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_NS: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_RANS:
3871  return true;
3872  default:
3873  return false;
3874  }
3875  }
3876 
3877  /*!
3878  * \brief Return true if a NEMO solver is in use.
3879  */
3880  bool GetNEMOProblem(void) const {
3881  switch (Kind_Solver) {
3882  case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER : case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
3883  return true;
3884  default:
3885  return false;
3886  }
3887  }
3888 
3889  /*!
3890  * \brief Return true if an AUSM method is in use.
3891  */
3892  bool GetAUSMMethod(void) const {
3893  switch (Kind_Upwind_Flow) {
3894  case UPWIND::AUSM : case UPWIND::AUSMPLUSUP: case UPWIND::AUSMPLUSUP2: case UPWIND::AUSMPLUSM:
3895  return true;
3896  default:
3897  return false;
3898  }
3899  }
